The paper deals with the analysis of news media and its coverage of world events, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), which deals with the analysis of social networks and information diffusion. The paper also involves NLP techniques for text analysis, which suggests the category cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also deals with the selection of reported events, which involves information retrieval (IR) techniques, suggesting the category cs.IR. The paper also uses embedding methods, which are commonly used in deep learning (DL) and representation learning, suggesting the category cs.DL. Finally, the paper deals with the analysis of multimedia content, which suggests the category cs.MM (Multimedia).
